RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOOD STORY shifted in and moved forward inside on or just off the rail early on the turn racing in behind the leaders, moved out five wide coming past the quarter pole, continued to drift out gradually throughout the lane and under steady urging and through a long drive edged past late. SKY BUY was well-placed stalking the pace, went four wide on the turn moving to challenge and take the lead at the quarter pole, was in command in upper stretch, drifted out just a bit, was outfinished but a clear second. AZTEC BAY was quick to the lead, set the pace racing off the rail in hand, faced outside pressure, was overtaken about the quarter pole, drifted out a bit in the stretch, kept on evenly late. CELTIC WAR CRY was lightly bumped at the start, pursued from outside four then three wide on the turn and off the leaders, moved to the rail at the top of the stretch, ran on inside for the minor award. VOODOO PRIESTESS broke outwardly bumping that rival lightly then in turn bumped by that one, shifted to the rail and tracked from inside, dropped back passing the seven-sixteenths, came out a bit for the drive, failed to rally. HEY RIRI exchanged light bumps on both sides at the start, raced between foes at the rear early, came into upper stretch on the rail, altered out at the three-sixteenths as a rival came in front, failed to rally. MIDSUMMER STORM switched outside the leader, moved forward to press that one from outside three deep coming past the five-eighths, began to lose ground on the turn, was guided out a bit past the five-sixteenths, floated six wide into upper stretch, continued to weaken.

ENTRY.COMMENT: switched out, press 3w 5/8, move out 5/16, float 6w, weakened

TRITONE GAL was bumped into a rival and pinched back at the start, brought up the rear, swung seven wide into upper stretch, failed to menace. LADY MOSLER attended the pace from outside, pressed four wide on the turn, came up empty.
